DICKEYA, POTATO AND SWEETPOTATO - UK, CHINA
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1] _Dickeya solani_ blackleg, potato - UK: (Northern Ireland)
[2] _Dickeya_ stem and root rot, sweetpotato - China: 1st report,
(Guangdong Province)

******
[1] _Dickeya solani_ blackleg, potato - UK: (Northern Ireland)
Date: 9 Nov 2010
Source: UTV News [edited]
<http://www.u.tv/News/Blackleg-found-on-NI-potatoes/6d749bd4-8458-4661-b804-a7517adfc1ba>


A new strain of the potato disease "blackleg" has been confirmed in
Northern Ireland, agriculture minister Michelle Gildernew has said.
Infected plants were discovered after an examination of 62 local crops was
carried out by the Agri-Food and Biosciences Institute (AFBI) and the
agriculture department [DARD].

The department says the outbreak has been "fully contained," and that
measures have been put in place to prevent further spread. Any machinery
and equipment that may have come into contact with the crop must be
disinfected before coming into contact with other potatoes. The affected
crop will be disposed of under the supervision of DARD.

The minister said that growers must notify the department in advance if
they plan to import seed [tubers] into the country. Growers should
carefully consider the risks of introducing seed from areas known to have
_Dickeya solani_.
[Additional news story:
<http://www.farminglife.com/farmingnews/New-strain-of-potato-disease.
6620070.jp>]

